FBIS3-23009 "jptot008__l94110" JPRS-TOT-94-008-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 1 March 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA YEMEN GPC Official Wounded in Attack in Maharrah 11 Feb JN1302104694 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in Arabic 0515 GMT 13 Feb 94 JN1302104694 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] Sanaa--[passage omitted] A responsible source at the Yemeni Ministry of Interior said last night that Colonel Yahya al-Jubi, director of political security in the Maharrah Governorate and member of the General People's Congress [GPC], was the target of an assassination attempt by unidentified gunmen who shot and wounded him near his house before escaping. Al-Jubi sustained several wounds in the attack, which took place the day before yesterday [11 February], according to the source. The source indicated that Col. al-Jubi is currently in the hospital intensive care unit, and that the security agencies are conducting extensive investigations to apprehend the assailants.
